    <description>
Composer-Setup downloads and installs [Composer](https://getcomposer.org), the PHP Dependency Manager, so you can use it easily from the command line.

* it looks for PHP on your computer (you need to have this installed)
* it adds PHP to the path
* it offers solutions to common PHP configuration problems
* it installs Composer globally - just type `composer` from any location to use it
* it lets you use the Command Prompt, Git Bash, Msys, Msys2 and Cygwin (including cygwin php)

Note: To keep Composer updated, run `composer selfupdate` from your terminal.    
